            We live in a hyper-connected digital world, yet loneliness
            and emotional distress are rising. Social media pressure,
            constant comparison, and online isolation can silently affect
            mental health, often going unnoticed.

            This project focuses on identifying early signs of self-harm 
            tendencies through emotional and behavioral analysis. By using
            technology to detect patterns of distress, the platform aims to
            promote awareness and encourage support for those who may be 
            silently struggling

